CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 13, 1957, pg. 2, reads: "Began 'Fourth' - Twin girls, Marva and Marsha Wheeler, were the first new arrivals at Montefiore Hospital on July Fourth. Mrs. Eugene Wheeler, of 7114 Mount Vernon St., cuddles her offspring brought to her by Nurse D. Harris.  The twins were born shortly before 2 A.M.  Marva's weight was six pounds, 11 ounces, while Marsha, who was born three minutes later, weighed five pounds, 12 ounces. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Eugene Wheeler holding newborn daughters Marva Wheeler and Marsha Wheeler, posed with nurse D. Harris in Montefiore Hospital, Pittsburgh
